						 <p>I like this one because it carries itself as something that <em>could</em> actually exist. I think how realistic and authentic the approach was (such as in the interview log) is what sold me especially. Given that everything in here is <em>grounded</em>, the sheer, contrasting &quot;What the fuck?&quot; factor of the Shell-Event is about as effective as it could possibly be (that is to say, very).</p> <p>Great work, Rockteeth, I always find myself enjoying your take on weirdness!</p> 
